Poland’s Budget Deficit Widens to 36% of 2011 Limit in February

-- B y   D o r o t a   B a r t y z e l
-- 
2011-03-15T14:09:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/poland-s-budget-deficit-widens-to-36-of-2011-limit-in-february.html
  Poland ’s central government budget
deficit widened to 14.4 billion zloty ($4.95 billion) at the end
of February, reaching 35.9 percent of the annual limit set in
this year’s budget bill.  The two-month deficit compared with 2.76 billion zloty, or
6.9 percent of the goal, at the end of January, the Warsaw-based
 Finance Ministry  said in an e-mailed statement today.  Revenue totaled 42 billion zloty, or 15.4 percent of the
annual target, while spending amounted to 56.4 billion zloty, or
18 percent of the plan.  The 2011 budget law caps the central government deficit at
40.2 billion zloty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dorota Bartyzel in Warsaw 
 dbartyzel@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net  